Question: What do you like/dislike about public transportation.
Answer:
Public transportation is a great way to explore a place. You get a chance to see what daily life is like and meet people from all walks of life. In addition, the opetation of public transportation reflects local policy, social norm and economic situation. It is also a great way to save money. However, public transportation can be unpleasant  sometimes. For instance, you have to share a limited space with a group of people; the bus may run out of schedule. More importantly, there are restrictions coming from time and routines.